title: Creating NIF files from SDTM data
text: Following regulatory standards, clinical study data commonly provided SDTM format, observation-based data tabulation format logically related observations organized topical collections (domains). SDTM defined maintained Clinical Data Interchange Standards Consortium (CDISC). support typical pharmacometric analyses, data different SDTM domains need aggregated single analysis data set. example, demographic pharmacokinetic concentration data DM PC domains required evaluate exposure age. complex analyses like population-level PK PK/PD analyses may include data, e.g., clinical laboratory, vital sign, biomarker data. NONMEM modeling software packages expect input data provided (long) tabular arrangement strict requirements formatting nomenclature variables (see, e.g., Bauer, CPT Pharmacometrics Syst. Pharmacol. (2019) introduction). input data file analyses sometimes casually referred ‘NONMEM input format’ ‘NIF’ file, hence name package. Contingent downstream analyses, variables analysis data set can easily automatically derived SDTM source data, e.g., ‘DOSE’ (administered dose) ‘DV’ (dependent variable observations), demographic covariates like ‘AGE’, ‘SEX’ ‘RACE’. fields input data set may require study-specific considerations, example calculation baseline renal hepatic function categories, definition specific treatment conditions study arm, encoding adverse events concomitant medications, categorical covariates. latter variables often need manual study-specific data programming, core NIF data set can cases generated quite standardized way. also manual addition analysis-specific fields substantially simplified functions nif package provides. Often, analysis data sets can thus created handful lines code. Even basic NIF data sets, missing data data inconsistencies, specifically relating date time fields, need resolved get analysis-ready data sets. frequently encountered analyzing preliminary data ongoing clinical studies fully cleaned. nif package provides number standardized imputation rules resolve issues. point later well separate vignette (vignette("nif-imputations")). Overall, nif package intended facilitate creation analysis data sets (‘NIF data sets’) SDTM-formatted clinical data.

title: Append observation events — add_observation
text: nif nif object. sdtm sdtm object. Needs least 'DM' 'VS' domains, domain observations come . domain domain character. testcd observation variable, character. analyte name analyte. Defaults 'testcd', NULL. parent name parent analyte observation character. Defaults value 'analyte' NULL. metabolite Observation metabolite, logical. cmt compartment observation numeric. subject_filter filtering apply DM domain. observation_filter filtering apply observation source data. cat xxCAT filter apply, character. scat xxSCAT filter apply, character. TESTCD_field xxTESTCD field. Defaults two-character domain name followed 'TESTCD', NULL. DTC_field field use date-time code observation. Defaults two-character domain name followed 'DTC', NULL. DV_field field use dependent variable. Defaults two-character domain name followed 'STRESN', NULL. coding_table Coding table translate categorical values numerical values, data frame. data frame must least one column matches column domain, numerical 'DV' column provides recoding result. factor Multiplier DV field, numeric. NTIME_lookup data frame two columns, column defines custom nominal time information target domain (e.g., 'PCELTM'), 'NTIME'. data frame left_joined observation data frame provide NTIME field. ntime_method field derive nominal time . Allowed values "TPT" "ELTM".Defaults xxTPT xx domain name, NULL. keep Columns keep, character. debug Include debug fields, logical. include_day_in_ntime logical. silent Suppress messages, logical. Defaults nif_option setting NULL. duplicates Selection deal duplicate observations respect USUBJID, ANALYTE DTC fields: 'stop': Stop execution produce error message 'ignore': Include duplicates data set 'identify': Return list duplicate entries 'resolve': Resolve duplicates, applying duplicate_function duplicate entries. duplicate_function Function resolve duplicate values, defaults mean. omit_not_done Delete rows xxSTAT "DONE, logical. na.rm Logical indicating whether remove NA values applying duplicate_function. Defaults TRUE.

Mappings must provided form: TESTCD ~ EXTRT TESTCD can xxTESTCD domain xx included sdtm object. See testcd() overview analytes domains. Formulae can also specify multiple observations associated one treatment, e.g., RS2023 + RS2023487A ~ EXAMPLINIB. Multiple mappings can given, separated commas. analyte name nif object automatically set respective TESTCD. IMPORTANT: multiple analytes specified treatment, implicitly assumed first analyte corresponds parent analyte treatment, e.g., case , 'RS2023' assumed analyte 'EXAMPLINIB' treatment parent compound.
